 To write a first person controller script in GDscript and apply it to a KinematicBody-node when using Godot Engine 3.x, follow these steps:

1. Create a new C# script in your project and name it "FirstPersonController.cs".
2. Open the script and add the following code:

```csharp
using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;

public class FirstPersonController : MonoBehaviour
{
    public Rigidbody rb;

    void Start()
    {
        rb = GetComponent<Rigidbody>();
    }

    void Update()
    {
        transform.Rotate(new Vector3(0, 0, 1) * Time.deltaTime);
        rb.MovePosition(transform.position + transform.forward * 5f * Time.deltaTime);
    }
}
```

3. In your scene, add a KinematicBody-node.
4. Drag and drop the "FirstPersonController.cs" script onto the KinematicBody-node.
5. In the Godot Engine 3.x scene, the KinematicBody-node will control the character's movement.

In Godot Engine 4.x, the equivalent to the KinematicBody-node is the "RigidBody" node. To apply the first person controller script to the RigidBody node, follow these steps:

